All 50 passengers on board an aeroplane owned by Dana Airlines Limited have been rescued after fire engulfed the tyres of the aircraft. The passengers however could no longer proceed with their scheduled flight from Port Harcourt to Lagos after the incident that happened on Monday. It was gathered that the plane with registration number 5N JOY was taxing to take off when fire wafted from its tyre compartment. The pilot was said to have stopped the plane and immediately evacuated the passengers with the help of the airport officials. A spokesperson of the airline, Kingsley Ezenwa, confirmed the incident saying no life was lost and no passenger sustained any injury.   Lagos residents condemn underage access to hotels, alcohol     Tucano fighter aircrafts: Group accuses Saraki of re-writing…     2023: Tinubu ‘ll change Nigeria’s story for good— Lagos…   He said: “Our aircraft with registration number 5N JOY operating flight 9J 344 from Port Harcourt to Lagos on the 2nd of May 2022 was set to take off when the pilot in command noticed an anomaly which he queried with the Air Traffic Control (ATC) before embarking on a ramp return in line with our strict safety operating procedures. “However, the impact on the brakes as a result of the aborted takeoff affected the aircraft tyres which sparked off while the aircraft was taxiing to repark “All 50 passengers onboard the aircraft disembarked safely and our maintenance team immediately grounded the aircraft pending the conclusion of their investigations. “Once again, we sincerely apologize to all the passengers on the flight for the inconveniences caused due to the eventual cancellation of the flight. “At Dana Air, the safety of our passengers and crew will remain a top priority in all aspects of our operations and we will continue to operate in accordance with the civil aviation regulations and global best practices”